# Fixture FM6b: Chained @base directives — each replaces the previous base.
#
# Hypothesis: An implementation that resolves relative IRIs against the
# document's first (rather than most-recently-declared) base will produce
# wrong absolute IRIs for triples after the second @base.
#
# Expected resolution:
#   After first @base  <http://example/a/>: <r1> -> <http://example/a/r1>
#   After second @base <http://example/b/>: <r2> -> <http://example/b/r2>
#   After third  @base <http://example/c/>: <r3> -> <http://example/c/r3>
#
# Divergence signal: FactOnlyIn if IRI resolution uses stale base.
#
# Spec: Turtle §2.2.

@base <http://example/a/> .
<r1> <p> <o> .

@base <http://example/b/> .
<r2> <p> <o> .

@base <http://example/c/> .
<r3> <p> <o> .
